text: Baden Chapman Teague (born 18 September 1944) is an Australian politician. He was a member of the Liberal Party. He served as a Senator for South Australia from 1977 until his retirement in 1996. Teague was born in Adelaide, South Australia. He married Katherine Jane Packard in 1972. The couple have three sons, including Josh Teague. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:Living people Category:Liberal Party of Australia Category:Members of the Australian Senate Category:People from Adelaide Category:Politicians from South Australia
